; A failing `(static-assert …)`. Rust's codegen returns
; `Err("static assertion failed: <msg>")`, rendered as
; `error: static assertion failed: static assertion failed` (the default message)
; and exits nonzero. The self-host used to hard-error with `UNIMPLEMENTED:` here;
; it must now render the real diagnostic (Divergence #3, src/codegen.rs +
; src/main.rs). The condition `(icmp-eq 1 2)` folds to 0, so the assert fires.
(static-assert (icmp-eq 1 2))
(defn main [] (-> i64) 0)
